definition.value: A mulberry is a fruit multiple from a mulberry plant
Bayberry is a sweet, crimson to dark purple-red, fruit from the Myrica rubra tree.

Vaccinium elliottii (Elliott's blueberry) is a species of Vaccinium in the blueberry group (Vaccinium sect. Cyanococcus). It is native to the southeastern and south-central United States, from southeastern Virginia south to Florida, and west to Arkansas and Texas.

Dulce de leche is a confection from Latin America prepared by slowly heating sweetened milk to create a substance that derives its flavour from the Maillard reaction, also changing colour, with an appearance and flavour similar to caramel.
A stew is a combination of solid food ingredients that have been cooked in liquid and served in the resultant gravy.
An inner core and growing bud of certain palm trees, including coconut, acai palm, sabal, and juçara
The fruit may derive from palm trees (notably coconut (Cocos nucifera), juçara (Euterpe edulis), Açaí palm (Euterpe oleracea), palmetto (Sabal spp.), and peach palm).
Junket is a milk-based dessert, made with sweetened milk and rennet, the digestive enzyme that curdles milk.
Bulgur is a cereal food made from the cracked parboiled groats of several different wheat species, most often from durum wheat.
A caffè mocha is a chocolate-flavored variant of a caffè latte
Chimichanga is a deep-fried burrito that is common in Tex-Mex and other Southwestern U.S. cuisine.
Tapioca pearls are pebble-sized spheres of tapioca; sizes range from about 1 mm to 8 mm in diameter, with 2–3 mm being the most common.
Nutrition drinks are beverages that promise a healthy balance of protein, carbohydrate, and fat.

"Canadian bacon" or "Canadian-style bacon" is the American name for a form of back bacon that is cured, smoked and fully cooked, trimmed into cylindrical medallions, and thickly sliced. "Canadian" bacon is made only from the lean eye of the loin and is ready to eat. Its flavor is described as more ham-like than other types because of its lean cut.

Back bacon is a cut of bacon that includes the pork loin from the back of the pig. It may also include a portion of the pork belly in the same cut. It is much leaner than side bacon made only from the pork belly.
A heart meat product is a food product deriving from heart organ(s).
A brain food product is a food product deriving from animal brain.

Stenodus nelma, known alternatively as the nelma, sheefish, inconnu or connie, is a commercial species of freshwater whitefish in the family Salmonidae. It is widespread in the Arctic rivers from the Kola Peninsula (White Sea basin) eastward across Siberia to the Anadyr River and also in the North American basins of the Yukon River and Mackenzie River.
A species of wheat (Triticum spelta).
A whole kernel of spelt (Triticum spelta)

Sweetbread is a culinary name for the thymus (also called throat, gullet, or neck sweetbread) or pancreas (also called stomach, belly or gut sweetbread), typically from calf (ris de veau) and lamb (ris d'agneau), and, less commonly, beef and pork.
Almond milk is a plant milk manufactured from almonds with a creamy texture and nutty flavor,
A poultry sandwich contains chicken, turkey or other poultry meat.
A seafood sandwich is a sandwich made with fish and/or other seafood ingredients.
Orange mint is a hybrid variety of mint grown for its fragrant leaves, and is a member of the Lamiaceae or Labiate family.
A species of flowering plant in the mint family Lamiaceae.
One or more pieces of chickens.
A bean food product harvested frrom the scarlet runner bean plant.
A bean pod harvested frrom the scarlet runner bean plant.
A species of flowering plant in the heath family.
A fruit of the longan tree (Dimocarpus longan).
A fruit of the Rambutan tree.

An onion that is harvested from the Welsh onion plant.
A variety of kale with a long tradition in Italian cuisine, especially that of Tuscany.
A subtropical marine fish, classified in family Serranidae, the groupers and sea basses. It is found in the eastern Atlantic Ocean, the Mediterranean Sea, and the Black Sea.
A whole raw nut with its shell intact.

A burger patty that does not contain meat or any such kind of meat. These burgers may be made from ingredients like beans, especially soybeans and tofu, nuts, grains, seeds or fungi such as mushrooms or mycoprotein.
A squash-like cucurbit grown for its immature fruit, a vegetable especially popular in South Asia. It is the only member of the genus Praecitrullus.
A food product from the seed of guarana plants.
A food product derived from fruit of the longan tree (Dimocarpus longan).

A food product derived from jojoba beans.
Ymer is a Danish soured milk product which has been known since 1930 and is made by fermenting whole milk with the bacterial culture Lactococcus lactis.
Crispbread is a flat and dry type of cracker, containing mostly rye flour.
